          id: 'aggregate-demand-multipliers', title: 'Aggregate Demand and Spending Multipliers', titleZh: '总需求与支出乘数',
          heading: 'Total planned spending at each price level', headingZh: '每个价格水平下的计划总支出',
          intro: 'Aggregate demand shows the total quantity of domestically produced final goods and services demanded at each price level. It slopes downward for three macroeconomic reasons: a lower price level raises real wealth and consumption; lowers money demand and interest rates, stimulating interest-sensitive spending; and makes domestic output relatively cheaper, increasing net exports. These are not the microeconomic substitution and income effects for one product. Aggregate demand equals planned consumption, investment, government purchases, and net exports.',
          introZh: '总需求表示每个价格水平下对国内最终产品与服务的总需求量。它向下倾斜有三个宏观原因：较低价格水平提高实际财富和消费；降低货币需求和利率，刺激利率敏感支出；使国内产品相对便宜，增加净出口。这不同于单一商品的微观替代效应和收入效应。总需求等于计划消费、投资、政府购买和净出口。',
          model: 'AD shifts when a non-price-level determinant changes: consumer confidence, wealth, taxes, expected income, interest rates caused outside a price-level movement, expected profitability, fiscal policy, foreign income, or exchange rates. Autonomous spending changes can be multiplied because one person’s expenditure becomes another’s income. The simple spending multiplier is $1/(1-MPC)$, and the simple tax multiplier is $-MPC/(1-MPC)$. The balanced-budget multiplier is one in the simple model. Leakages through saving, taxes, and imports make real-world multipliers smaller.',
          modelZh: '非价格水平因素变化会移动 AD，包括消费者信心、财富、税收、预期收入、由价格水平之外因素引起的利率变化、预期盈利、财政政策、外国收入和汇率。自主支出变化会被乘数放大，因为一人的支出成为另一人的收入。简单支出乘数为 $1/(1-MPC)$，简单税收乘数为 $-MPC/(1-MPC)$。简单模型中的平衡预算乘数为 1。储蓄、税收和进口等漏出使现实乘数更小。',
          math: ['AD=C+I+G+(X-M)', 'MPC+MPS=1', 'k=\\frac{1}{1-MPC}=\\frac{1}{MPS}', 'k_T=-\\frac{MPC}{1-MPC}'],
          skill: 'Decide whether an event is a movement along AD or a shift. A change in the price level itself causes movement; a change in spending at every price level shifts AD. For multiplier calculations, identify the initial autonomous change, choose the correct multiplier, and preserve the sign. A tax cut increases disposable income but only the MPC share is initially spent, so its multiplier magnitude is smaller than the government-purchase multiplier.',
          skillZh: '先判断事件造成沿 AD 移动还是 AD 移动。价格水平本身变化造成沿曲线移动；每个价格水平下支出变化使 AD 移动。乘数计算要确定初始自主变化、选择正确乘数并保留符号。减税提高可支配收入，但只有 MPC 部分最初用于消费，因此税收乘数绝对值小于政府购买乘数。',
          note: 'A change in the price level does not shift aggregate demand. It changes real balances, interest rates, and net exports along the existing AD curve.',
